Document: AnimationLibrary
Path: godot/classes/class_animationlibrary.rst
Summary: Methods for managing animations in an AnimationLibrary, including adding, retrieving, and modifying animations.

Method: add_animation(name: StringName, animation: Animation) → Error. Adds the animation to the library, accessible by the key name.

Method: get_animation(name: StringName) → Animation. Returns the Animation with the key name. If the animation does not exist, null is returned and an error is logged. Note: Returns null and logs an error when the animation is not found.

Method: get_animation_list() → Array<StringName>. Returns the keys for the Animations stored in the library.

Method: get_animation_list_size() → int. Returns the key count for the Animations stored in the library.

Method: has_animation(name: StringName) → bool. Returns true if the library stores an Animation with name as the key.

Method: remove_animation(name: StringName). Removes the Animation with the key name.

Method: rename_animation(name: StringName, newname: StringName). Changes the key of the Animation associated with the key name to newname.